cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper discusses multi-task learning in the context of reinforcement learning for robotic control tasks. This suggests that it could fall under several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). However, given the focus on learning and optimization, cs.LG and cs.RO are the most likely categories. The use of simulated environments and benchmarking also suggests a focus on empirical evaluation, which further supports the likelihood of cs.LG and cs.RO. The mention of computer vision is brief and only in the context of comparing multi-task learning success across domains, so cs.CV is less likely. Finally, while the paper does touch on control systems, it is not the primary focus, so cs.SY is the least likely category.
